.SH NAME
gnb-edit - Edit an existing alias


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgnb edit   [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit an existing alias in the configuration.
Example:
  gnb edit gs "git status --short --branch"
  gnb edit --global gs "git status"


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--global\fP[=false]
	Save to global config

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for edit


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgnb(1)\fP


